---
import InfoLayout from '../layouts/InfoLayout.astro';
---

<InfoLayout
  title="Privacy policy — Flipkart Assist"
  eyebrow="Privacy policy"
  heading="What we keep, where it goes, and how to clear it."
  intro="Flipkart Assist is a demo project, so this policy is short and honest rather than long and vague."
>
  <h2>What we collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Your chat messages</strong> — everything you type into the assistant.</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Booking details you provide</strong> — if you walk through the mock booking
      flow, the name, address, and phone number you enter are held in your session.
      They can be entirely made up; nothing checks them against reality.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>A session ID</strong> — a random identifier kept in your browser's
      sessionStorage so a page refresh can restore your conversation.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not use analytics, advertising trackers, or cookies. There are no accounts and
    no sign-in.
  </p>

  <h2>Where your data goes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Groq</strong> — your messages are sent to Groq's API to generate the
      assistant's replies, subject to Groq's own data policies.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Our backend</strong> — conversation state is stored in a server-side
      session database so the agents can remember context between turns.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>External product APIs</strong> — when the catalog can't answer, product
      names from your query may be sent to third-party catalog APIs (MobileAPI,
      TechSpecs) and a web search API (Tavily) to fetch live specs and prices.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we never collect</h2>
  <p>
    Payment is a mock flow — a simple arithmetic challenge stands in for a payment
    gateway. <strong>No card number, UPI ID, or any payment credential is ever asked
    for, transmitted, or stored.</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>Clearing your data</h2>
  <p>
    Click <strong>New conversation</strong> in any chat, or switch categories, and your
    session is discarded and a fresh one starts. Closing the browser tab clears the
    session ID and cached transcript from your browser.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>
    Ask anything about this policy via the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
  </p>
</InfoLayout>
